### =============================================================================
### ✅ OTP FLOW (Parent)
### =============================================================================

### [6] Send OTP — expect 200, same message regardless of phone registered or not
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+919876543210"
}

###

### [7] Verify OTP — expect 200 + tokens
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+919876543210",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###

### [8] Wrong OTP — expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+919876543210",
  "otp": "000000"
}

###

### [9] Exceed OTP attempts (run [8] 5 times then this) — expect 429
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+919876543210",
  "otp": "000000"
}

###

### =============================================================================
### ✅ REFRESH TOKEN
### =============================================================================

### [10] Valid refresh — expect 200 + new token pair
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### [11] Replay old refresh token after rotation (reuse detection)
###      Run [10] first, then paste the OLD refreshToken below
###      Expect 401 "Security alert" + ALL sessions wiped for that user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "PASTE_OLD_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###

### [12] Invalid refresh token — expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "thisisnotavalidtoken"
}

###

### =============================================================================
### ✅ LOGOUT
### =============================================================================

### [13] Valid logout — expect 200
###      Check server logs: session cache + user cache should be invalidated
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### [14] Use same access token after logout — expect 401 (blacklisted)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### [15] Logout with no refresh token — expect 200 (still valid, just no refresh cleanup)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{}

###

### [16] Logout with no auth token — expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###
